[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626965&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626965&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

If I have a node which does not have it's cache primed, 
but has forwarders in it's boot file, it never tries the 
forwarders.  It outputs to debug that it has no root 
entry in it's cache and gives up.  Is There a reason why
it should not try the forwarders?   

Also, if you put a node in slave mode, it will initially 
try to contact a nameserver other than the specified 
forwarders, and if this fails, then revert only to the 
specified forwarders.  This seems contrary to the d
ocumentation (surprise :=) !) and to the intent of the 
slave switch.

Any comments or helpful suggestions?  I'm trying to run 
named on nodes without priming their cache, but while 
providing forwarders.  On Apollo's, with our distributed 
file system, this allows for a single copy of the named 
boot, cache, and local files for all the users on a 
specific net or collection of nets.  Nice for the 
un-netwise user and the system administrator.

Thanks in advance,

